{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"b2353a3c-5d44-4e07-9522-5a657b4afc4c","content":"The `Directory.Build.props` enables the Roslyn shared compilation server (`VBCSCompiler`), which keeps the compiler warm between builds.\n\n## Summary\n\n| Technique | Saves | How |\n|---|---|---|\n| `dotnet watch build` | ~2–3s | Hot MSBuild process, auto-rebuild |\n| `--no-restore` | ~0.5–1s | Skips redundant NuGet restore |\n| `DOTNET_CLI_USE_MSBUILD_SERVER=1` | ~1–2s | Persistent MSBuild server |\n| `MSBUILDDISABLENODEREUSE=0` | ~0.5–1s | Reuses MSBuild worker nodes |\n| `UseSharedCompilation` | ~0.3–0.5s | Reuses Roslyn compiler process |\n\nFor the fastest inner loop, combine `dotnet watch build` with the environment variables. This should bring CLI incremental builds from 2–4s down to near-instant, matching Visual Studio.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"3e80b635-4a04-4c82-9b48-64ee2844add1","outputTokens":241,"requestId":"7805:16A6CA:7F252C1:8D52758:69EABD94"},"id":"456658bf-e06e-4541-a78d-eceec2706f72","timestamp":"2026-04-24T00:47:23.137Z","parentId":"7a16be84-b438-4710-bf23-83c348570dbf"}
